reviews.review:
A disappointing end to a trilogy that never seemed to know where it was going, and suffered from sharply contrasting creative direction.  It's fun in places, but the whole is much less than the sum of its parts.  It left me just feeling sad at the wasted potential.

Never has empty spectacle felt so empty.
Good movie, fixes a lot of what Rian Johnson ruined.

great action sequences, pays homage to the entire saga, gives a decent ending to it all, but was very fast paced, chopping sequencing, questionable writing, it truly highlights the difference between the sequels from the prequels- the prequels had great vision, but awful, hiseous character development, while the sequels had seemingly no vision (movies had twists because it seemed the writers didn't even know where they were going) but the character development was a key focus and honestly well done. another sign of the times in this movie is that it's clear they probably had 6 hours of content that they tried to cut and splice into less than 3... overall not a bad movie, but keep expectations in check. it's not Avengers: Endgame by any stretch... but it is better than Batman v Superman.

Worse movie I ever went to theaters for.

The Room has a more coherent and relatable plot
Ignore the critics, it’s Totally Fresh!
The criticism it’s getting is correct, but it still was a fun movie. The action, humor and visuals were probably the best of the new trilogy.

In all my years of watching the STAR WARS Saga, I have never seen a movie quite like this one. This episode is one of a kind. It had all the action and all the suspense that will leave everyone on the edge of their seats. It also pays tribute to all of the greatest moments in STAR WARS history. As the story of the Skywalker legacy comes to a close, it will leave a huge impact on many that have been there since the beginning. The way it ended will leave a huge smile on everyone's faces. To be honest, THE RISE OF SKYWALKER has a special place in my life as my all time favorite episode in the STAR WARS saga. This movie delivers.
Must see ! Idk why people hate it
